column4: Which is the National tree of United Kingdom?
column10: The oak is the national tree of England representing strength and endurance. The Royal oak and Oak Apple Day commemorate the escape of King Charles II from the grasps of the parliamentarians after his father's execution
column11: he hid in an oak tree to avoid detection before making it safely into exile.

column4: Which is the National flower of Iran?
column10: The tulip is a Eurasian and North African genus of perennial, bulbous plants in the lily family. It is an herbaceous herb with showy flowers, of which around 75 wild species are currently accepted.

column4: What is the national bird of Iraq?
column10: The chukar partridge or chukar is a Eurasian upland gamebird in the pheasant family Phasianidae.

column4: Red kangaroo is which Country's National animal?
column10: The eastern grey kangaroo (Macropus giganteus) is less well-known than the red (outside Australia), but the most often seen, as its range covers the fertile eastern part of the country.

column4: The National animal of Finland is
column10: The brown bear is a large bear distributed across much of northern Eurasia and North America and is the largest land-based predator on earth.

column4: Mango Tree is which country's National tree?
column10: The mango is the national fruit of India, Pakistan, and the Philippines. It is also the national tree of Bangladesh. In India, harvest and sale of mangoes is during March–May and this is annually covered by news agencies.

column4: Which  is the Maldives National flower.
column10: The rose is the national flower of the United States, the United Kingdom and the Maldives. It is also the official flower of several states and the province of Alberta. The rose once served as Honduras' national flower as well.

column4: The National tree of Maldives is
column10: The National Tree of the Republic of Maldives is the "Dhivehi Ruh" (Coconut Palm). All the islands throughout the Republic support a dense growth of the palm.

column4: The National bird of Greece is
column10: The little owl is a bird that inhabits much of the temperate and warmer parts of Europe, Asia east to Korea, and north Africa.

column4: Which is the national tree of Australia?
column10: Acacia pycnantha, commonly known as the golden wattle, is a tree of the family Fabaceae native to southeastern Australia.
